The paper deals with the k-Vertex-Disjoint Paths problem on planar directed graphs, which involves graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are likely sub-categories. The problem also involves finding pairwise vertex-disjoint paths, which can be related to graph theory and combinatorics, making cs.GT (Graph Theory) and cs.CC (Combinatorics) possible sub-categories as well.
